external_knowledge:
- 'Marathon runners of the road' refers to trucks with the highest total distance driven; 
- 'Roadworthiness' refers to the current operational status of the trucks (e.g., active, in maintenance, retired); 
- 'Visited the garage' refers to the maintenance event; 
- 'Lead navigators' refers to the drivers who have driven the most hours for each of the top trucks.

External Knowledge:
- 'broken the speed barrier' refers to an average speed of more than 50; 
- 'covered long distances' means having driven a total distance of more than 1000.

sql:
SELECT truck_model
FROM trucks
WHERE capacity = (SELECT MAX(capacity) FROM trucks);
